<title>MEXICO: Mexican pension firms sign up 4.05 mln workers.</title>
<headline>Mexican pension firms sign up 4.05 mln workers.</headline>
<dateline>MEXICO CITY 1997-06-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Mexico's 17 pension fund management firms (Afores) signed up a total of 4.051 million workers as of June 12, with Afore Bancomer nearing the one-million mark, the National Retirmement Savings System Commission said on Monday.</p>
<p>It issued the following list detailing total affiliations and market share for each Afore:</p>
<p>   Afore			     Total	Market share (%)</p>
<p>-------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>   Bancomer			 932,994	   23.03</p>
<p>   Banamex			  734,764	   18.13</p>
<p>   Santander Mexicano	   556,349	   13.73</p>
<p>   Profuturo GNP		  483,502	   11.93</p>
<p>   Bital			    464,517	   11.46</p>
<p>   Garante			  278,043	    6.86</p>
<p>   Banorte			  223,285	    5.51</p>
<p>   Bancrecer Dresdner	   136,020	    3.36</p>
<p>   Previnter			 77,007	    1.90</p>
<p>   Inbursa			   52,792	    1.30</p>
<p>   Atlantico Promex		46,434	    1.15</p>
<p>   Genesis			   19,687	    0.49</p>
<p>   Afore XXI			 16,214	    0.40</p>
<p>   Confia Principal		10,360	    0.26</p>
<p>   Tepeyac			    9,951	    0.25</p>
<p>   Zurich			     8,675	    0.21</p>
<p>   Capitaliza			 1,208	    0.03</p>
<p>------------------------------------------------- ((-- Cyntia Barrera Diaz, Mexico City newsroom 525 728 9549))</p>
